  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 17 high, 6 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 16 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP). Network hotspots: Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Kaunas (KUN/EYKA) and 3 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and snow / blowing snow. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and 9 others.",
